# Technical Problem Statement: Design a Chat Analytics System

##Background
We operate a chat analytics platform that handles millions of conversations daily. Our current challenge is building a system to analyze, cluster, and derive insights from these conversations.

##Scale
  - 2M+ new messages per day
  - Average conversation:
      User messages: 3-5 messages, ~50 bytes each
  - Al responses: 3-5 responses, ~2KB each
  - The unique characteristic of our data is the asymmetric nature of conversations - user messages are typically short (1-10 sentences) while Al responses are much longer (5-10 paragraphs).
  - Need to maintain 1 year of conversation history
    Messages growing 50% QoQ

  System Requirements
1. Data Processing
• Ingest and store messages immediately
• Handle variable-length messages efficiently
• Maintain conversation context and flow
• Support for metadata extraction and updates
2. Clustering & Analysis
• Real-time conversation clustering
• Topic detection and categorization
• Pattern recognition across conversations
• Support for custom analysis pipelines
3. Query & Access
• Fast search across conversations
• Complex analytical queries
• Support for pattern matching
• Efficient access to related conversations
